		<h4><a name="q1">What Is It?</a></h4>
		<div class="answer"> The Application Shop is a 3<sup>rd</sup> party managed site for Orange customers to purchase applications for use on their handsets. An application is a piece of software you can download onto your phone for personal use.
			<p>A link to the Application Shop will be accessible from the Orange internet site and from Orange World on a mobile Device.</p>
			<p>Orange has tried and tested the applications on this site and is satisfied they are compatible with Orange technology.</p>
			<p><a class="backToTop" href="#top">back to top</a></p>
		</div>
		<!--answer 2-->
		<h4><a name="q2">How Does It Work?</a></h4>
		<div class="answer"> Only Applications compatible with and suitable for your device will be offered to you.
			<p><u>Via the Web</u><br />
				On the Application Shop you can identify yourself entering your Orange mobile number and handset type into the relevant section of the Application Shop web page.</p>
			<p><u>Via WAP</u><br />
				The Application Shop will be available via the device to all users with devices capable of downloading applications. Your handset will be automatically identified.</p>
			<p><u>Purchase Example</u><br />
				An example of how to buy an application via WAP on a Sony Ericsson device is shown below:</p>
			<ol>
				<li>Select "Applications" from Orange World home page or the Tools tab.</li>
				<li>Select one of the links on the Applications page such as one of the featured items, What's new or Categories.</li>
				<li>Select an application title.</li>
				<li>You will see the application details including the price of the application.</li>
				<li>Select Buy. </li>
				<li>On the Payment page select the payment option provided, e.g. 'Pay on my phone bill' and select continue.</li>
				<li>Select "Download now" to begin the download of the application.</li>
				<li>The application will begin to download and will automatically install. After the install is complete, you will see the option to 'Start Now?'.</li>
				<li>If you select 'Yes' the application will start.</li>
				<li>If you select 'No' you will be back to the Purchase Completed page. Here you can click on "Continue shopping" to go back to the Applications home page.</li>
			</ol>
			<p><a class="backToTop" href="#top">back to top</a></p>
		</div>
